  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "SSC stands for Staff Selection Commission. This organization in India conducts various exams for recruitment to different Group \"B\" and Group \"C\" posts in various Ministries/Departments/Organizations of the Government of India.\n\nHere's a breakdown of the postings you can get under SSC, categorized by some of the major exams they conduct:\n\n**1. SSC CGL (Combined Graduate Level Examination):**  This is arguably the most popular SSC exam.  It recruits for a wide range of posts.\n\n*   **Group B Gazetted:**\n    *   Assistant Enforcement Officer (Directorate of Enforcement, Department of Revenue)\n    *   Assistant (Various Ministries/Departments like CSS, Ministry of External Affairs, AFHQ)\n    *   Inspector (Central Excise, Preventive Officer, Examiner - CBIC)\n    *   Assistant Audit Officer (Indian Audit & Accounts Department under CAG)\n    *   Assistant Accounts Officer (Indian Audit & Accounts Department under CAG)\n\n*   **Group B Non-Gazetted:**\n    *   Assistant Section Officer (CSS)\n    *   Inspector (Department of Post, CBI)\n    *   Sub Inspector (CBI, NIA)\n    *   Assistant/Superintendent (Various Organizations)\n    *   Divisional Accountant (CAG)\n    *   Statistical Investigator Grade-II (M/o Statistics & Programme Implementation)\n    *   Auditor (CAG, CGDA, Others)\n    *   Accountant/Junior Accountant (CAG, CGDA, Others)\n    *   Senior Secretariat Assistant / Upper Division Clerks (Central Govt. Offices/Ministries other than CSCS cadres.)\n\n*   **Group C:**\n    *   Tax Assistant (CBDT, CBIC)\n    *   Upper Division Clerk (Government Departments)\n\n**2. SSC CHSL (Combined Higher Secondary Level Examination):**  This exam recruits for posts requiring 10+2 qualification.\n\n*   **Lower Division Clerk (LDC)/ Junior Secretariat Assistant (JSA):** (Central Government Offices) These are entry-level clerical posts.\n*   **Postal Assistant/ Sorting Assistant (PA/SA):** (Department of Posts)  Handle mail sorting and customer service.\n*   **Data Entry Operator (DEO):** (Various Government Departments and Offices) Input and manage data. DEOs are further categorized into DEO and DEO Grade A, based on skill tests.\n\n**3. SSC MTS (Multi Tasking Staff Examination):** This is for Group \"C\" non-gazetted, non-ministerial posts.\n\n*   **Multi Tasking Staff (MTS):**  (Various Central Government Departments/Offices)  This involves tasks such as:\n    *   Maintaining files and records\n    *   Routine office work (photocopying, faxing)\n    *   Assisting in computer-related tasks\n    *   Cleaning and upkeep of the office\n    *   Delivering documents within the office\n\n**4. SSC CPO (Central Police Organisation Examination):**  This exam is for recruitment to Sub-Inspectors in various police forces.\n\n*   **Sub-Inspector (SI) in Delhi Police**\n*   **Sub-Inspector (SI) in Central Armed Police Forces (CAPFs):** (CRPF, BSF, ITBP, CISF, SSB)\n\n**5. SSC JE (Junior Engineer Examination):**  This is for engineering graduates and diploma holders.\n\n*   **Junior Engineer (Civil, Mechanical, Electrical, Quantity Surveying & Contracts):** (Various Government Departments like CPWD, MES, CWC)\n\n**6. SSC Stenographer Grade C & D Examination:** This exam is for stenographers.\n\n*   **Stenographer Grade C:** (Ministries/Departments of the Central Government) Higher-level stenographic duties.\n*   **Stenographer Grade D:** (Ministries/Departments of the Central Government)  Lower-level stenographic duties.\n\n**7. SSC GD Constable (General Duty Constable):** This exam is for recruitment in CAPFs and other organizations.\n\n*   **Constable (GD) in:**\n    *   Border Security Force (BSF)\n    *   Central Industrial Security Force (CISF)\n    *   Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF)\n    *   Indo-Tibetan Border Police (ITBP)\n    *   Sashastra Seema Bal (SSB)\n    *   National Investigation Agency (NIA)\n    *   Secretariat Security Force (SSF)\n    *   Rifleman (GD) in Assam Rifles\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Eligibility Criteria:**  Each exam has specific age, educational qualification, and physical standards (where applicable) criteria.\n*   **Pay Scale:** Pay scales vary depending on the Group (B, C, etc.) and the specific post.  Check official notifications for details.\n*   **Job Location:** Postings can be anywhere in India.\n*   **Promotions:**  There are opportunities for promotion based on performance and seniority within the departments.\n*   **Transfer Policy:** Transfer policies vary depending on the department.\n*  **Official Notifications are Key:**  Always refer to the official notification released by SSC for the specific exam you're interested in. The notification contains the most up-to-date and accurate information regarding vacancies, eligibility, syllabus, exam pattern, and other important details.\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's highly recommended to visit the official SSC website:  **ssc.nic.in**\n",
